<subSubSection id="188A36BB8D899532F282178CE9272A88" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" type="comments">
<paragraph id="19E3034B3A0465F1E45720A04F291A74" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E62831C202F888B29AEDA873CE55F5B4" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">
<normalizedToken id="2C42D5DF75F793F7744B849FD3869A20" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName id="7248D6DCD5907F44652485F2314DAA90" authority="K.Romaschenko, 2019" authorityName="K.Romaschenko" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eriosella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eriosella caduca" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caduca">
<emphasis id="F86D3FCECBE74D453651EE59107394B4" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Eriosella caduca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is thought to be a hybrid between 
<taxonomicName id="6B553B7460D6E0C5C8F50560D82DE903" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eriocoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eriocoma hymenoides" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hymenoides">
<emphasis id="95001B67C3CD477B823E070C8386A5B0" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Eriocoma hymenoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="41B06794A29C39A705C49155CA756DA9" authorityName="Barkworth" authorityYear="1990" baseAuthorityName="Trin." class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Nassella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Nassella viridula" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="viridula">
<emphasis id="A524D78DC9AA2D336B03ABA53D9206AF" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Nassella viridula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It can be separated from 
<taxonomicName id="D02D56A240ACA168A0D45B5FAB95FA29" genus="E." lsidName="E. hymenoides" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" rank="species" species="hymenoides">
<emphasis id="41C716359D4F2A5EF779F0158BAE4CDC" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">E. hymenoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having shorter hairs on the lemma and panicles with ascending branches (not divergent), and from 
<taxonomicName id="AAE884E2321F2BB0EE741242DEA75E3A" genus="N." lsidName="N. viridula" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" rank="species" species="viridula">
<emphasis id="1FEB5FD948518EF39189900053056FEF" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">N. viridula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having longer lemma hairs, paleas 2/3-3/4 as long as the lemma, and readily deciduous lemmatal awns (
<bibRefCitation id="99D7F9BED788975030789FACA07A7E2A" author="Barkworth, ME" editor="Barkworth, ME" journalOrPublisher="Oxford Universtiy Press, New York" pageId="20" pageNumber="109" pagination="109 - 186" refId="B3" refString="Barkworth, ME, 2007. 10. Stipeae Dumort. In: Barkworth, ME, Capels, KM, Long, S, Anderton, LK, Piep, MB, Eds., Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 1. Oxford Universtiy Press, New York: 109 - 186" title="10. Stipeae Dumort." volumeTitle="Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 1." year="2007">Barkworth 2007</bibRefCitation>
). Another species similar to 
<normalizedToken id="E6EC3A155ABB34FE386C8F0C1D35ECD1" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName id="976CD5F0B848B61BA5811F57F9F79451" authority="K.Romaschenko, 2019" authorityName="K.Romaschenko" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eriosella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eriosella caduca" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caduca">
<emphasis id="5CB984FE671AA1E9748B0625A84AF0E7" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Eriosella caduca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<taxonomicName id="8F897062AD3209505C29EBE1B78974A2" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eriocoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eriocoma bloomeri" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bloomeri">
<emphasis id="45A1228F799111D7FE2DA9BCE98A2EC2" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="97">Eriocoma bloomeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the latter species has glabrous sheaths, shorter ligules, 5-veined lemmas, awns with a sub-plumose lower section below the bend, and anthers with more numerous apical hairs (
<bibRefCitation id="9A4391ADE70CB135E02DF070F3BCFD20" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/j.1537-2197.1943.tb14731.x" author="Johnson, BL" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Botany" pageId="21" pageNumber="110" refId="B19" refString="Johnson, BL, Rogler, GA, 1943. A cyto-taxonomic study of an intergeneric hybrid between Oryzopsis hymenoides and Stipa viridula. American Journal of Botany 30(1): 49-56. https://doi.org/10.1002/j.1537-2197.1943.tb14731.x" title="A cyto-taxonomic study of an intergeneric hybrid between Oryzopsis hymenoides and Stipa viridula. American Journal of Botany 30 (1): 49 - 56." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/j.1537-2197.1943.tb14731.x" year="1943">Johnson and Rogler 1943</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
